transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, this is Olivia speaking, who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 2: Yes, Arthur Curtis.

Speaker 1: Hi, Arthur. How are you?

Speaker 2: I'm doing good.

Speaker 1: How are you doing?

Speaker 2: Good.

Speaker 1: Good.

Speaker 2: Thank you for asking.

Speaker 1: How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: I'm going to take advantage of this account, my account I have with you all.

Speaker 1: Sorry, you want to what?

Speaker 2: I'm taking the balance of my balance on this account.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I mean, you know, your prescription is available to you, you just need, whenever you are ready to place another order, you just need to let us know and update your credit card information.

Speaker 2: Okay, so right now, I don't owe anything, right?

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: I mean, this is not an automatic, you know what I'm saying, this is not an automatic charge, it's just up on my, asking for it.

Speaker 1: So the prescriptions, they do come with refills, if you don't want to receive them super regularly, you certainly don't have to, you can always place the prescription and its refills on hold for up to six months at a time, just because six months is when the prescription would expire, if we didn't refill it.

Speaker 2: So whenever you do place your next order, if you want to set it up differently, you just have to let us know.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: Right now, I just want to put it on hold for an hour and a half, because this is not automatic for my account, is it?

Speaker 1: So it would have been, but I just placed it on hold for you until the end of July.

Speaker 2: So yeah, you won't be charged or be receiving anything until you call us to place that order yourself and update the info.

Speaker 1: Okay, I appreciate that.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Great.

Speaker 2: Well, thank you, Arthur.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, have a great day.
